[A map of the various TB regions of Michigan may be found at http://www.michigan.gov/documents/MDA_TB_ZoneSplitStateMap_87803_7.pdf.

Michigan may be found on the interactive HealthMap at http://healthmap.org/r/1nDW.

Bovine tuberculosis has plagued the northern region of the lower peninsula of Michigan for some time. The surveillance on TB has included cervids for quite some time. Surveillance and risk involves both deer and cattle in trying to rid the state of this disease. – Mod.TG]
